The paper deals with the generation of synthetic 3D scenes and 2D images for the purpose of training and benchmarking computer vision and robotics algorithms. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses a stochastic grammar to generate the scenes, which is a technique commonly used in Graphics (cs.GR) research. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of the generated scenes for robotics algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
